Alejandro Espinosa-Rada

My name is Alejandro Espinosa-Rada and I am a Postdoctoral Researcher at the Social Networks Lab in ETH Zrich. Before arriving in Zrich, I did my PhD in Sociology at the Mitchell Centre for Social Network Analysis at the University of Manchester. Also, I was an adjunct assistant professor in which I taught courses related to social network analysis at the Departments of Sociology (PUC and UAH), the Department of Computer Science (PUC), and the Department of History (USACH).

Main areas of interests: Group Dynamics, Sociology of Social Networks, Sociology of Science and Knowledge/Science of Science/Social Studies of Science and Technology, and Network Modelling.

You can also check Knitting Networks, the podcast of the Social Network Science (chapters in Spanish or English) hosted by Francisca Ortiz and myself. The podcast is sponsored by the International Network for Social Network Analysis (INSNA).

Other projects:

  • Co-PI at the Social Networks and Socio-ecological Sustainability Project (SNA-SES). Project funded by FONDECYT program N1220560
